cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.MA 

The paper discusses the use of AI components in remote manipulation tasks, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed benchmarks and metrics are aimed at evaluating the effectiveness of these shared controllers, which involves the use of AI techniques such as machine learning and human-computer interaction (cs.AI, cs.HC). The paper also mentions the application of these controllers in industrial settings, which suggests a systems engineering perspective (cs.SY). Finally, the empirical evaluation of the proposed controller involves comparing it to a manually operated manipulator, which could involve the use of optimization techniques (cs.MA).
